==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mona
<hw>Mo"na</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[CF. Sp. & Pg.
<ets>mona</ets>, fem. of <ets>mono</ets> a monkey, ape.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A small, handsome, long-tailed West American
monkey (<spn>Cercopithecus mona</spn>). The body is dark olive, with a
spot of white on the haunches.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Monachal</ent>⟦br⟧
